SIMPLE: pointed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pointed
<hw>Point"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sharp; having a sharp point; <as>as, a <ex>pointed</ex> rock</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by sharpness, directness, or pithiness of expression; terse; epigrammatic; especially, directed to a particular person or thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His moral pleases, not his <qex>pointed</qex> wit.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pointed arch</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>an arch with a pointed crown.</cd> -- <col><b>Pointed style</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a name given to that style of architecture in which the pointed arch is the predominant feature; -- more commonly called <altname>Gothic</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Point"ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Point"ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pointel</ent>⟦br⟧
